<HEADLINE>
APEC MARKET SURVEILLANCE WORKSHOP TO BE HELD MAY 24
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  May 23 (CNA) 05/23/07  19:51:47 (By Ruth Wang)
</P>
<P>
The Bureau of Standards, Metrology and Inspection will hold an
APEC Market Surveillance Workshop May 24-25 for international
exchanges among Asia-Pacific countries, a spokesman for the
bureau said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
According to the spokesman, more than 160 representatives of
academy, industry, consumer protection groups and organizations
on market surveillance from 16 member economies of the Asia-
Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC) forum, will participate in
Thursday's workshop in Taipei.
</P>
<P>
The workshop will touch upon three subjects: regulatory
framework; views of industry and consumers; and the practice of
market surveillance programs, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
There will also be a keynote speech given by Nancy Nord, acting
chairwoman of the Consumer Product Safety Commission of the
Untied States. Nord has signed a memorandum of understanding with
Taiwan for cooperation associated with consumer product safety
matters.
</P>
<P>
Participants will be able to share their experience in market
surveillance to further boost information exchanges and
cooperation among Asia-Pacific countries.
</P>
